Azure Cloud Project – Secure File Sharing Architecture Implementation

Name: Varinder Pal Singh

Project Title: Secure Cloud-Based File Sharing System using Azure


⸻

1. Introduction

This project demonstrates the implementation of a secure cloud architecture using Microsoft Azure. The objective is to deploy a file-sharing application (OwnCloud) on a public subnet and a database server (MySQL) on a private subnet, ensuring security, scalability, and controlled access.

The architecture follows best practices by isolating sensitive resources in a private subnet and enabling secure communication using a bastion-like approach and NAT Gateway.

⸻

2. Architecture Overview

The solution includes:

* Virtual Network (VNet)
* Public Subnet (Application Layer)
* Private Subnet (Database Layer)
* NAT Gateway (for outbound internet access from private subnet)
* Network Security Groups (NSG)
* Ubuntu Virtual Machines
* OwnCloud (Application)
* MySQL (Database)

⸻

3. Implementation Steps

⸻

Step 1: Resource Group Creation

* Navigated to Azure Portal → Resource Groups
* Created a resource group named P1-RG
* Selected region: [Enter Region]

⸻

Step 2: Virtual Network and Subnet Configuration

* Created Virtual Network:
    * Name: P1VNET
    * Address Space: 10.0.0.0/16
* Created Subnets:
    * Public Subnet: 10.0.1.0/24
    * Private Subnet: 10.0.2.0/24

⸻

Step 3: NAT Gateway Configuration

* Created NAT Gateway:
    * Name: P1-NAT
    * Associated with Private Subnet
* Configured:
    * Public IP
    * Public IP Prefix (/30)
* Attached NAT Gateway to Private Subnet

⸻

Step 4: Network Security Groups (NSG)

AppNSG (Application Layer)

* Allowed inbound ports:
    * 22 (SSH)
    * 80 (HTTP)

DbNSG (Database Layer)

* Allowed inbound ports:
    * 22 (SSH)
    * 3306 (MySQL)

⸻

Step 5: Virtual Machine Deployment

Application Server (Public VM)

* OS: Ubuntu 22.04
* Size: Standard B1s
* Subnet: Public Subnet
* Public IP: Enabled
* NSG: AppNSG

⸻

Database Server (Private VM)

* OS: Ubuntu 20.04
* Size: Standard B1s
* Subnet: Private Subnet
* Public IP: Disabled
* NSG: DbNSG

⸻

Step 6: Secure Access Configuration

* Connected to Application VM using SSH
* Copied database PEM key to Application VM
* Accessed Database VM via Application VM using private IP

⸻

Step 7: MySQL Installation (Database Server)

Executed the following commands:

sudo apt update
wget https://d6opu47qoi4ee.cloudfront.net/azure_install_mysql.sh
sudo chmod 700 azure_install_mysql.sh
sudo apt install dos2unix -y
sudo dos2unix azure_install_mysql.sh
sudo ./azure_install_mysql.sh

⸻

Step 8: OwnCloud Installation (Application Server)

Executed:

sudo apt update
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php -y
sudo apt update

Installed dependencies and configured Apache.

Downloaded and deployed OwnCloud:

cd /var/www/html
sudo rm *
sudo wget https://download.owncloud.com/server/stable/owncloud-complete-latest.tar.bz2
sudo tar -xjf owncloud-complete-latest.tar.bz2
sudo chown -R www-data:www-data owncloud
sudo systemctl restart apache2

⸻

Step 9: Application Testing

* Accessed application using browser:
    http:///owncloud
* Verified successful deployment of OwnCloud interface

